nic <i>Ava</i>, or of Old French and Middle English <i>Avice</i> (see   Avis  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Eve","meanings":["English (Essex) and Dutch: from the Middle English personal name <i>Eve</i> (from Latin <i>Eva</i>), of Biblical Hebrew origin (meaning ‘life’). According to the Book of Genesis, this was the name of the first woman, and in some cases the name may have been acquired by someone (invariably a man) who had played the part in a drama dealing with the Creation."]},{"name":"Heavilin","meanings":["Altered form of English   Evelyn  , with the addition of excrescent <i>H-</i>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":15,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Evelyn was born about 1440, in Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, England. He had at least 3 sons with Mrs William Evelyn. He died in 1490, in London, England, at the age of 51."},"et":{"about 1440–1490":"umbes 1440–1490","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","1472–1508":"1472–1508","1474–Male":"1474–Surnud","1478–Male":"1478–Surnud","1440–1490":"1440–1490","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1474":"1474","1440":"1440","about 1478":"umbes 1478","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","1508":"1508","about 1440":"umbes 1440","10 January 1472":"10. jaanuar 1472","about 1474":"umbes 1474","1490":"1490","Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, England":"Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, England","London, England":"London, England"},"fi":{"about 1440–1490":"noin 1440–1490","1450–Female":"1450–Kuollut","1472–1508":"1472–1508","1474–Male":"1474–Kuollut","1478–Male":"1478–Kuollut","1440–1490":"1440–1490","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1474":"1474","1440":"1440","about 1478":"noin 1478","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","1508":"1508","about 1440":"noin 1440","10 January 1472":"10. tammikuuta 1472","about 1474":"noin 1474","1490":"1490","Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, England":"Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, England","London, England":"London, England"},"fr":{"about 1440–1490":"environ 1440–1490","1450–Female":"1450–Décédée","1472–1508":"1472–1508","1474–Male":"1474–Décédé","1478–Male":"1478–Décédé","1440–1490":"1440–1490","1478":"1478","1455":"1455","1474":"1474","1440":"1440","about 1478":"environ 1478","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","1508":"1508","about 1440":"environ 1440","10 January 1472":"10 janvier 1472","about 1474":"environ 1474","1490":"1490","Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, England":"Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, Angleterre","London, England":"Londres, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Evelyn est né environ 1440, à Harrow on the Hill, Middlesex, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 3 fils avec Mrs William Evelyn. Il est décédé en 1490, à Londres, Angleterre, à l’âge de 51 ans."},"de":{"about 1440–1490":"um 1440–1490","1450–Female":"1450–Verstorben","1472–1508":"1472–1508","1474–Male"